modules.description: This module implements the WAMP (Web Application Messaging Protocol) message types and serialization for OCaml, handling core operations like message construction and type conversion. It works with data types such as `msgtyp` for message kinds, `msg` for structured messages, and `role` for client roles, using `Uri.t`, `dict`, and `list` for structured data. Concrete use cases include creating and parsing WAMP messages for real-time communication in distributed systems, such as publishing events, subscribing to topics, and handling session lifecycle events like hello and welcome.
